  "prompt": "How much do furniture salesmen make?",
  "response": "The earnings of furniture salespeople can vary widely based on several factors, including location, experience, the type of store they work for, and their compensation structure. Typically, furniture salespeople earn a combination of a base salary and commissions based on their sales performance. Here are some general insights:\n\n1. **Base Salary:** The base salary for furniture salespeople can range from around $20,000 to $40,000 annually. In many cases, this is supplemented with commissions.\n\n2. **Commission:** Commissions can significantly boost earnings. It often ranges from 2% to 10% of the sales they generate. High-performing salespeople in busy or high-end stores can earn much more from commissions than their base salaries.\n\n3. **Total Income:** Combining base salary and commissions, many furniture salespeople earn between $30,000 and $60,000 per year. However, in high-end or high-volume retail environments, skilled salespeople can earn $70,000 or more annually.\n\n4. **Benefits and Incentives:** Some positions may offer additional benefits, such as health insurance, retirement plans, and personal discounts on furniture.\n\nIt's important to note that these figures can vary greatly. For precise information, it's advisable to look at job listings in your area, check salary websites like Glassdoor or Payscale, or speak directly with others in the industry.",
